
PREREQUISITES:
-------------
Building for Windows is only tested for the MinGW cross-compilation environment, http://mingw-cross-env.nongnu.org


BUILDING:
--------

1. Build libtcod. It is included in this source tree.

  cd libtcod
  mkdir build
  cd build
  cmake ..
  make

1.1 Install libtcod files:

  cp src/libtcod.so .../diggr-roguelike
  cp ../libtcodpy.py .../diggr-roguelike


2. Download and build SuperCollider sources: (optional, if you want sound)

2.1. Check out SC sources from the repo:

  git clone --recursive git://supercollider.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/supercollider/supercollider

2.2. Build SC with a minimal required set of dependencies: (Replace '/prefix' with a real directory.)

  cd supercollider
  mkdir build
  cd build
  AUDIOAPI=portaudio cmake -DFFT_GREEN=ON -DNO_LIBSNDFILE=ON -DSC_QT=OFF -DSUPERNOVA=OFF -DNO_AVAHI=ON -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX:PATH=/prefix/SuperCollider/ -DSC_WII=OFF -DSC_EL=OFF ..
  make
  make install/strip

2.3. Copy SC binaries to 'diggr-roguelike/sound/':

  cd .../diggr-roguelike/
  cd sound
  cp /prefix/SuperCollider/bin/scsynth .
  cp /prefix/SuperCollider/lib/libscsynth.so.1 .  
  cp -rf /prefix/SuperColliderlib/SuperCollider/plugins/ .




